%pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType, DoubleType
from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline, PipelineModel

udf_transform_uvi = udf(lambda uvi: float(np.log(uvi)), DoubleType())

nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/uv_srs.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

df_iluv = nt.join(uv, ['date', 'time'])\
            .join(cl, 'date')\
            .withColumn('month', udf_month('date'))\
            .withColumn('weather', udf_weather('month'))\
            .where('uvi > 0 and uvi < 12 and date < "2019-03-01"')\

weather = 0
if weather == 0:
    w = 'Spring'
elif weather == 1:
    w = 'Summer'
elif weather == 2:
    w = 'Fall'
elif weather == 3:
    w = 'Winter'

# ds_e = df_iluv.where('weather = %d' % weather)\
#               .select('illum', 'uvi').sort('illum')\
#               .withColumn('t_uvi', udf_transform_uvi('uvi'))

ds_e = df_iluv.select('illum', 'uvi').sort('illum')\
              .withColumn('t_uvi', udf_transform_uvi('uvi'))
              
assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['illum'], outputCol='features')
asm_ds = assembler.transform(ds_e)
ds_train, ds_test = asm_ds.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], 2)
lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.3, elasticNetParam=0.8,
                      featuresCol='features', labelCol='t_uvi',
                      predictionCol='predic_uvi')
lrModel = lr.fit(ds_train)
# pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
# pipelineModel_exp = Pipeline.fit(ds_train)
# res_pl_train = pipelineModel_exp.transform(ds_train)

coef = float(lrModel.coefficients[0])
intcpt = float(lrModel.intercept)
smry = lrModel.summary
print('train> r2: %.4f' % smry.r2)
print('train> RMSE: %.4f' % smry.rootMeanSquaredError)

# test dataset
ds_res_test = lrModel.transform(ds_test)
ds_res_test.cache()
# ds_res_test.show()

# evaluate
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol='t_uvi', predictionCol='predic_uvi')
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(ds_res_test)
mse = evaluator.setMetricName('mse').evaluate(ds_res_test)
r2 = evaluator.setMetricName('r2').evaluate(ds_res_test)
mae = evaluator.setMetricName('mae').evaluate(ds_res_test)
print("test> rmse:%.4f, mse:%.4f, r2:%.4f, mae:%.4f" % (rmse, mse, r2, mae))

# pipeline
pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
plmodel_exp = pipeline_exp.fit(ds_e)  # input dataset before assembling

x = list(map(lambda r: r['illum'], ds_e.select('illum').collect()))
y = list(map(lambda r: r['uvi'], ds_e.select('uvi').collect()))
yf = list(map(lambda v: np.exp(intcpt) * np.exp(coef * v), x))

# plotting
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax.scatter(x, y, marker='.', label='illum_uvi')
# ax.plot(x, yf, 'r-', linewidth=3.0)
ax.set_xlim([0, 140000])
ax.set_ylim([0, 12])
ax.set_xlabel('Illumanace [lx]')
ax.set_ylabel('UV Index')
ax.set_title('UV Index by illuminance')
ax.legend()
plt.show()

%pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType, DoubleType
from pyjake.basemodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline, PipelineModel

udf_transform_uvi = udf(lambda uvi: float(np.log(uvi)), DoubleType())

nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/uv_srs.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

df_iluv = nt.join(uv, ['date', 'time'])\
            .join(cl, 'date')\
            .withColumn('month', udf_month('date'))\
            .withColumn('weather', udf_weather('month'))\
            .where('uvi > 0 and uvi < 12 and date < "2019-03-01"')\

weather = 0
if weather == 0:
    w = 'Spring'
elif weather == 1:
    w = 'Summer'
elif weather == 2:
    w = 'Fall'
elif weather == 3:
    w = 'Winter'
    
ds_e = df_iluv.where('weather = %d' % weather)\
              .select('date', 'time', 'illum', 'uvi')\
              .withColumn('time', udf_10min('time'))\
              .groupby(['date', 'time']).avg('illum', 'uvi')\
              .withColumnRenamed('avg(illum)', 'illum')\
              .withColumnRenamed('avg(uvi)', 'uvi')\
              .withColumn('t_uvi', udf_transform_uvi('uvi'))\
              .select('illum', 'uvi', 't_uvi').sort('illum')
              
ds_e.show()
              
assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['illum'], outputCol='features')
asm_ds = assembler.transform(ds_e)
ds_train, ds_test = asm_ds.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], 2)
lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.3, elasticNetParam=0.8,
                      featuresCol='features', labelCol='t_uvi',
                      predictionCol='predic_uvi')
lrModel = lr.fit(ds_train)
# pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
# pipelineModel_exp = Pipeline.fit(ds_train)
# res_pl_train = pipelineModel_exp.transform(ds_train)

coef = float(lrModel.coefficients[0])
intcpt = float(lrModel.intercept)
smry = lrModel.summary
print('train> r2: %.4f' % smry.r2)
print('train> RMSE: %.4f' % smry.rootMeanSquaredError)

# test dataset
ds_res_test = lrModel.transform(ds_test)
ds_res_test.cache()
# ds_res_test.show()

# evaluate
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol='t_uvi', predictionCol='predic_uvi')
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(ds_res_test)
mse = evaluator.setMetricName('mse').evaluate(ds_res_test)
r2 = evaluator.setMetricName('r2').evaluate(ds_res_test)
mae = evaluator.setMetricName('mae').evaluate(ds_res_test)
print("test> rmse:%.4f, mse:%.4f, r2:%.4f, mae:%.4f" % (rmse, mse, r2, mae))

# pipeline
pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
plmodel_exp = pipeline_exp.fit(ds_e)  # input dataset before assembling

x = list(map(lambda r: r['illum'], ds_e.select('illum').collect()))
y = list(map(lambda r: r['uvi'], ds_e.select('uvi').collect()))
yf = list(map(lambda v: np.exp(intcpt) * np.exp(coef * v), x))

# plotting
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax.scatter(x, y, marker='.', label='illum_uvi')
ax.plot(x, yf, 'r-', linewidth=3.0)
ax.set_xlim([0, 140000])
ax.set_ylim([0, 12])
ax.set_xlabel('Illumanace [lx]')
ax.set_ylabel('UV Index')
ax.set_title('UV Index by illuminance "%s"' % w)
ax.legend()
plt.show()

%pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType, DoubleType
from pyjake.basemodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline, PipelineModel

udf_transform_uvi = udf(lambda uvi: float(np.log(uvi)), DoubleType())

nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/uv_srs.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

df_iluv = nt.join(uv, ['date', 'time'])\
            .join(cl, 'date')\
            .withColumn('month', udf_month('date'))\
            .withColumn('weather', udf_weather('month'))\
            .where('uvi > 0 and uvi < 12 and date < "2019-03-01"')\

weather = 0
if weather == 0:
    w = 'Spring'
elif weather == 1:
    w = 'Summer'
elif weather == 2:
    w = 'Fall'
elif weather == 3:
    w = 'Winter'
    
ds_e = df_iluv.where('weather = %d' % weather)\
              .select('illum', 'uvi').sort('illum')\
              .withColumn('t_uvi', udf_transform_uvi('uvi'))
assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['illum'], outputCol='features')
asm_ds = assembler.transform(ds_e)
ds_train, ds_test = asm_ds.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], 2)
lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.3, elasticNetParam=0.8,
                      featuresCol='features', labelCol='t_uvi',
                      predictionCol='predic_uvi')
lrModel = lr.fit(ds_train)
# pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
# pipelineModel_exp = Pipeline.fit(ds_train)
# res_pl_train = pipelineModel_exp.transform(ds_train)

coef = float(lrModel.coefficients[0])
intcpt = float(lrModel.intercept)
smry = lrModel.summary
print('train> r2: %.4f' % smry.r2)
print('train> RMSE: %.4f' % smry.rootMeanSquaredError)

# test dataset
ds_res_test = lrModel.transform(ds_test)
ds_res_test.cache()
# ds_res_test.show()

# evaluate
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol='t_uvi', predictionCol='predic_uvi')
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(ds_res_test)
mse = evaluator.setMetricName('mse').evaluate(ds_res_test)
r2 = evaluator.setMetricName('r2').evaluate(ds_res_test)
mae = evaluator.setMetricName('mae').evaluate(ds_res_test)
print("test> rmse:%.4f, mse:%.4f, r2:%.4f, mae:%.4f" % (rmse, mse, r2, mae))

# pipeline
pipeline_exp = Pipeline(stages=[assembler, lr])
plmodel_exp = pipeline_exp.fit(ds_e)  # input dataset before assembling

x = list(map(lambda r: r['illum'], ds_e.select('illum').collect()))
y = list(map(lambda r: r['uvi'], ds_e.select('uvi').collect()))
yf = list(map(lambda v: np.exp(intcpt) * np.exp(coef * v), x))

# plotting
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax.scatter(x, y, marker='.', label='illum_uvi')
ax.plot(x, yf, 'r-', linewidth=3.0)
ax.set_xlim([0, 140000])
ax.set_ylim([0, 12])
ax.set_xlabel('Illumanace [lx]')
ax.set_ylabel('UV Index')
ax.set_title('UV Index by illuminance "%s"' % w)
ax.legend()
plt.show()

%pyspark

from pyjake.basemodule import udf_dnt2dt

df_iluv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///tmp/ntuv_cl.parquet')\
               .withColumn('datetime', udf_dnt2dt('date', 'time'))\
               .drop('date', 'time').select('datetime', 'illum', 'uvi')
solar_angle = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///sun/angle_calc.parquet')\
                   .withColumn('datetime', udf_dnt2dt('date', 'time'))\
                   .drop('date', 'time').select('datetime', 'solar_zenith')

df = df_iluv.join(solar_angle, 'datetime')
df.show()
df.createOrReplaceTempView('iluvsz')
